<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"The term limit comes about relativ=
e to a number of topics from several different branches of mathematics. A s=
equence x_1,x_2,... of elements in a topological space X is said to have li=
mit x provided that for each neighborhood U of x, there exists a natural nu=
mber N so that x_n in U for all n&gt;=3DN. This very general definition can=
 be specialized in the event that X is a metric space, whence one says that=
 a sequence {x_n} in X has limit L if for all epsilon&gt;0, there exists a =
natural number...">
