lfram&nbsp;</span>Notebook</span></a>
</div>
<!-- Begin Content -->
<div class=3D"entry-content">
<p>
The term limit comes about relative to a number of topics from several diff=
erent branches of mathematics.
</p>
<p>
A <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Sequence.html">sequence</a> <img=
 src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline1.svg" c=
lass=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0=
" width=3D"69" height=3D"21" alt=3D"x_1,x_2,..."> of elements in a <a href=
=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/TopologicalSpace.html">topological
 space</a> <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit=
/Inline2.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:10=
0%" border=3D"0" width=3D"15" height=3D"21" alt=3D"X"> is said to have limi=
t <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline3.=
svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"x"> provided that for each <a href=
=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Neighborhood.html">neighborhood</a> <img =
src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline4.svg" cl=
ass=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0"=
 width=3D"15" height=3D"21" alt=3D"U"> of <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wol=
fram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline5.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=
=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" =
alt=3D"x">, there exists a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Natural=
Number.html">natural number</a> <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/i=
mages/equations/Limit/Inline6.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-hei=
ght:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"14" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N">=
 so that <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/I=
nline7.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%=
" border=3D"0" width=3D"50" height=3D"21" alt=3D"x_n in U"> for all <img sr=
c=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline8.svg" clas=
s=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" w=
idth=3D"42" height=3D"21" alt=3D"n&gt;=3DN">. This very general definition =
can be specialized in
 the event that <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/=
Limit/Inline9.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-wid=
th:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"15" height=3D"21" alt=3D"X">
 is a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/MetricSpace.html">metric spa=
ce</a>, whence one says that a sequence
 <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline10.=
svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"28" height=3D"21" alt=3D"{x_n}"> in <img src=3D"https://ma=
thworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline11.svg" class=3D"inlinefor=
mula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"15" he=
ight=3D"21" alt=3D"X"> has limit <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/=
images/equations/Limit/Inline12.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-h=
eight:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"11" height=3D"21" alt=3D"L=
"> if for all <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Li=
mit/Inline13.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-widt=
h:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"36" height=3D"21" alt=3D"epsilon&gt;0">, ther=
e exists a natural number <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/=
equations/Limit/Inline14.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:1=
00%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"46" height=3D"22" alt=3D"n_0 in N=
"> so that
</p>
<div>
