<p>
for all <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/In=
line15.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%=
" border=3D"0" width=3D"44" height=3D"22" alt=3D"n&gt;=3Dn_0">. In many com=
monly-encountered
 scenarios, limits are unique, whereby one says that <img src=3D"https://ma=
thworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline16.svg" class=3D"inlinefor=
mula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"11" he=
ight=3D"21" alt=3D"L"> is <i>the</i> limit of <img src=3D"https://mathworld=
.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline17.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" s=
