leSpace.html">first-countable</a>.
</p>
<p>
A function <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit=
/Inline38.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:1=
00%" border=3D"0" width=3D"34" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f(z)">
 is said to have a finite limit <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/i=
mages/equations/Limit/Inline39.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-he=
ight:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"112" height=3D"22" alt=3D"c=
=3Dlim_(z-&gt;a)f(z)">
 if, for all <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Lim=
it/Inline40.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width=
:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"35" height=3D"21" alt=3D"epsilon&gt;0">,
 there exists a <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/=
Limit/Inline41.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-wi=
dth:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"36" height=3D"21" alt=3D"delta&gt;0">
 such that <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit=
/Inline42.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:1=
00%" border=3D"0" width=3D"95" height=3D"21" alt=3D"|f(z)-c|&lt;epsilon"> w=
henever <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/In=
line43.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%=
" border=3D"0" width=3D"99" height=3D"21" alt=3D"0&lt;|z-a|&lt;delta">. Thi=
s form of definition is sometimes called
 an <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Epsilon-DeltaDefinition.html">=
epsilon-delta definition</a>. This can
 be adapted to the case of infinite limits as well: The limit of <img src=
=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline44.svg" clas=
s=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" w=
idth=3D"34" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f(z)"> as <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wo=
lfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline45.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" styl=
e=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"8" height=3D"21"=
 alt=3D"z">
 approaches <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limi=
t/Inline46.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:=
100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"9" height=3D"21" alt=3D"a">
 is equal to <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Lim=
it/Inline47.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width=
:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"27" height=3D"21" alt=3D"+infty">
 (respectively <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/L=
imit/Inline48.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-wid=
th:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"27" height=3D"21" alt=3D"-infty">)
 if for every number <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equat=
ions/Limit/Inline49.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;m=
ax-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"42" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N&gt;0">
 (respectively <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/L=
imit/Inline50.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-wid=
th:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"42" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N&lt;0">),
 there exists a number <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equ=
ations/Limit/Inline51.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%=
;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"8" height=3D"21" alt=3D"delta">
 depending on <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Li=
mit/Inline52.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-widt=
h:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"14" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N">
 for which <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit=
/Inline53.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:1=
00%" border=3D"0" width=3D"67" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f(z)&gt;N"> (respective=
ly, <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline=
54.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" bo=
rder=3D"0" width=3D"67" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f(z)&lt;N">) whenever <img src=
=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline55.svg" clas=
s=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" w=
idth=3D"99" height=3D"21" alt=3D"0&lt;|z-a|&lt;delta">. Similar adjustments=
 can be made to define
 limits of functions <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equat=
ions/Limit/Inline56.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;m=
ax-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"34" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f(z)">
 when <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inli=
ne57.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" =
border=3D"0" width=3D"58" height=3D"21" alt=3D"z-&gt;+/-infty">.
</p>
<p>
Limits may be taken from below
</p>
