nfimumLimit.html">infimum
limit</a>.
</p>
<p>
<a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Indeterminate.html">Indeterminate<=
/a> limit forms of types <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/e=
quations/Limit/Inline85.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:10=
0%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"41" height=3D"21" alt=3D"infty/inf=
ty"> and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/I=
nline86.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100=
%" border=3D"0" width=3D"29" height=3D"21" alt=3D"0/0"> can often be comput=
ed with <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/LHospitalsRule.html">L'Hos=
pital's
 rule</a>. Types <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations=
/Limit/Inline87.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-w=
idth:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"34" height=3D"21" alt=3D"0=C2=B7infty">
 can be converted to the form <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/Limit/Inline88.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-heig=
ht:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"29" height=3D"21" alt=3D"0/0"=
>
 by writing
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
