">
<div id=3D"eqn8" class=3D"eqnum">
(8)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
Types <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inli=
ne89.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" =
border=3D"0" width=3D"16" height=3D"21" alt=3D"0^0">, <img src=3D"https://m=
athworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Limit/Inline90.svg" class=3D"inlinefo=
rmula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"22" h=
eight=3D"21" alt=3D"infty^0">, and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.co=
m/images/equations/Limit/Inline91.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max=
-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"20" height=3D"21" alt=3D=
"1^infty"> are treated by introducing a dependent variable
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
